snippet.textDisplay:
nvidia took the wrong approach if they wanted miners to buy their mining specific cards; The mining specific cards are garbage in terms of mining efficiency compared to the regular RTX series cards.. So I don't see why miners would buy the mining specific cards unless the stocks of regular RTX cards have run dry.. As for the mining efficiency cap they're trying to introduce on the rtx3060... it'll fail miserably, I give it a week before miners figure out a workaround once the capped drivers are released.

Instead nvidia should've made those mining specific cards wildly more efficient than the current RTX series cards, they should also MASS produce those cards & sell them to actual consumer level miners. The previous run of mining specific cards nvidia made were 99% sold to bigtime mining farms, so barely any of those mining specific cards made in into the hands of regular consumer level miners, hence forcing those miners (and there are alot!) to keep on buying up stocks of regular video cards.. let's hope they learned from their mistakes

snippet.textDisplay:
I've been messing with  a chromebook for like a month now and my hatred for it grows every time I go to do something with it. ChromeOS doesn't have much of anything worthwhile I can actually do with it directly, it seems. It's one that doesn't support android apps and seems to be limited to Crouton for running Linux. 
Linux has been very hit or miss on functionality, there's not much space leftover to do anything besides office and daily driver stuff like video playback is very hit or miss to put it mildly. Hell, I can't even get things like "package manager" to run correctly.

If there's something I'm missing that makes ChromeOS itself worthwhile over Linux, Android, MacOS, or Windows, someone please feel free to let me know.
